 pp. 347-360; Lear, C.H., Elderfield, H., Wilson, P.A., Cenozoic deep-sea temperatures and global ice volumes from Mg/Ca in Benthic Foraminiferal Calcite (2000) Science, 287, pp. 269-272; Li, H.-C., Ku, T.-L., δ13 C-δ18O covariance as a paleohydrological indicator for closed-basin lakes (1997) Palaeogeogr. Palaeoclimatol. Palaeoecol., 133, pp. 69-80; Magyar, I., Geary, D.H., Müller, P., Paleogeographic evolution of the Late Miocene Lake Pannon in Central Europe (1999) Palaeogeogr. Palaeoclimatol. Palaeoecol., 147, pp. 151-167; Mandic, O., Harzhauser, M., Steininger, F., Roetzel, R., RCMNS 2005 Excursion C: Miocene of the Eastern Alpine Foredeep - The Bohemian Massive Southeastern Margin (2005) Nat. Hist. Mus. Excursion Guides, 46, pp. 1-53; Mátyás, J., Burns, S.J., Müller, P., Magyar, I., What can stable isotopes say about salinity? An example from the late Miocene Pannonian Lake (1996) Palaios, 11, pp. 31-39; Meller, B., Karpo-Taphocoenosen aus dem Karpat des Korneuburger Beckens (Unter-Miozän; Niederösterreich) (1998) Beitr. Paläontol., 23, pp. 85-121; Piller, W.E., Harzhauser, M., The Myth of the Brackish Sarmatian Sea (2005) Terra Nova, 17, pp. 450-455; Pisera, A., Miocene reefs of the Paratethys: A review (1996) SEPM, 5, pp. 97-104; Reinhardt, E.G., Fitton, R.J., Schwarcz, H.P., Isotopic (Sr, O, C) indicators of salinity and taphonomy in marginal marine settings (2003) J. Foramin. Res., 33, pp. 262-272; Rodriguez, C., Flessa, K.W., Tellez-Duarte, M.A., Dettman, D.L., Aliva-Serrano, G.A., Macrofaunal and isotopic estimates of the former extent of the Colorado River estuary, Upper Gulf of California, Mexico (2001) J. Arid Environ., 49, pp. 183-193; Rögl, F., Palaeogeographic considerations for Mediterranean and Paratethys Seaways (Oligocene to Miocene) (1998) Ann. Naturhist. Mus. Wien, 99 A, pp. 279-310; Schöne, B.R., Flessa, K.W., Dettman, D.L., Goodwin, D.H., Upstream dams and downstream clams: Growth rates of bivalve mollusks unveil impact of river management 